{"entries":[{"id":"tsk-jer-28-intro","title":"Jeremiah 28 — Chapter Introduction","author":"R. A. Torrey (editor)","reference":{"book":"JER","chapterStart":28,"verseStart":0,"chapterEnd":28,"verseEnd":0},"content":"<p>/scripRef> God creates heaven and earth; 3 the light; 6 the firmament; 9 separates the dry land; 14 forms the sun, moon, and stars; 20 fishes and fowls; 24 cattle, wild beasts, and creeping things; 26 creates man in his own image, blesses him; 29 grants the fruits of the earth for food.</p>\n<p>beginning. Pr 8:22-24; 16:4; Mr 13:19; Joh 1:1-3; Heb 1:10; 1Jo 1:1 God. Ex 20:11; 31:18; 1Ch 16:26; Ne 9:6; Job 26:13; 38:4; Ps 8:3; 33:6,9 Ps 89:11,12; 96:5; 102:25; 104:24,30; 115:15; 121:2; 124:8; 134:3 Ps 136:5; 146:6; 148:4,5; Pr 3:19; 8:22-30; Ec 12:1; Isa 37:16; 40:26 Isa 40:28; 42:5; 44:24; 45:18; 51:13,16; 65:17; Jer 10:12; 32:17 Jer 51:15; Zec 12:1; Mt 11:25; Ac 4:24; 14:15; 17:24; Ro 1:19,20 Ro 11:36; 1Co 8:6; Eph 3:9; Col 1:16,17; Heb 1:2; 3:4; 11:3; 2Pe 3:5 Re 3:14; 4:11; 10:6; 14:7; 21:6; 22:13 without. Job 26:7; Isa 45:18; Jer 4:23; Na 2:10 Spirit. Job 26:14; Ps 33:6; 104:30; Isa 40:12-14 God. Ps 33:6,9; 148:5; Mt 8:3; Joh 11:43 Let. Job 36:30; 38:19; Ps 97:11; 104:2; 118:27; Isa 45:7; 60:19; Joh 1:5,9 Joh 3:19; 2Co 4:6; Eph 5:8,14; 1Ti 6:16; 1Jo 1:5; 2:8 that. 10,12,18,25,31; Ec 2:13; 11:7 the light from the darkness. Heb. between the light andbetween the darkness.</p>\n<p>Day, and. 8:22; Ps 19:2; 74:16; 104:20; Isa 45:7; Jer 33:20; 1Co 3:13; Eph 5:13 1Th 5:5 And the evening and the morning were. Heb. And the eveningwas, and the morning was. 8,13,19,23,31 Let there. 14,20; 7:11,12; Job 26:7,8,13; 37:11,18; 38:22-26; Ps 19:1; 33:6,9 Ps 104:2; 136:5,6; 148:4; 150:1; Ec 11:3; Jer 10:10,12,13; 51:15 Zec 12:1 firmament. Heb. expansion. divided. Pr 8:28,29 above. Job 26:8; Ps 104:10; 148:4; Ec 11:3 and it. 9,11,15,24; Mt 8:27 God. 5,10; 5:2 evening. 5,13,19,23,31 Job 26:7,10; 38:8-11; Ps 24:1,2; 33:7; 95:5; 104:3,5-9; 136:5,6 Pr 8:28,29; Ec 1:7; Jer 5